  "special": {
    "title": "Give it a burl.",
    "description": "Reload throws the gun forward; it ricochets off enemies and surfaces for about 1.5 seconds without exploding. It then reverses, slows, and returns, homing onto the nearest enemy in its path. It explodes on contact during the return or after about 3.5 seconds. Reload explosion damage (grenade): card damage x unused ammo x 1.5. Red text: Give it a burl. (+100% weapon damage.)"
  },
  "notes": "Detonates once it has travelled back as far as it flew out; if you stand still and it hits nothing, it can explode on you. Move or use cover. At max range it randomly hooks left or right before returning. Only seeks targets on the way back, limiting effective range. Often clips an enemy then explodes beside them rather than on impact. Can lock onto destructibles and even airborne rockets. Always spawns with the fixed sight. Great for the High-Flying Hurler achievement/trophy on flying targets.",
